Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Filed: Original Transcript of Preliminary Hearing ( 20 pages) commencing 07-28-2022 by Amy De La Rosa.

Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen in court for Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo.  Attorney Samuel E. Simpson appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for final pretrial.  Case remains in trial posture.  State's offer stated on the record and rejected by the defendant.  State revokes offer.  Court addressed speedy trial demand expiration.  Argument heard.  Court's findings stated on the record.  Court grants continuance of the speedy trial demand to 12-05-2022.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Jury trial remains scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo not in court, in custody.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen appeared by video for Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo.  Attorney Samuel E. Simpson appeared by video for State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for status conference.  State requests a new jury trial date due to a scheduling conflict with an essential witness.  Court rescheduled jury trial.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Final pretrial remains scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 1:30 pm.  The final pretrial may be heard via Zoom. Zoom meeting information provided to parties.
Jury trial scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Court set a status date upon request from the State.  Parties notified of date.  Status conference scheduled for October 7, 2022 at 10:30 am.  This hearing will be heard via Zoom. Zoom meeting information provided to parties. This hearing may be streamed live on Dacast at the Court's discretion:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/a8cc2343-9b62-c309-778f-fa846faecb6a.
Received and Filed:  State's Supplemental Witness List.
Received and Filed:  State's Notice of Expert Testimony.
Received and Filed.
Received and Filed:  State's Motion in Limine.
Received and Filed:  State's Requested Jury Instructions.

Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo not in court, in custody.  Attorney Sylvan Jaspen appeared by video for Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo.  Attorney Patrick O'Keefe appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for status conference.  Defense entered a speedy trial demand on 8-24-2022.  Court set final pretrial and jury trial dates.  Court ordered all substantive motions to be filed by 9-30-2022 and all responses to be filed by 10-28-2022 or they will be deemed waived.  Defense requests a bail/bond hearing date.  Court instructed defense to file a bail motion if any circumstances have changed.  Court does not set a bail/bond hearing at this time. 
 Case adjourned to Branch 40.
Final pre-trial scheduled for October 28, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Jury trial scheduled for November 14, 2022 at 09:00 am.

Defendant enters a SPEEDY TRIAL DEMAND. 
Speedy expires 11-22-2022.
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for LEVEL 5 SUPERVISION.  All other previously ordered conditions of bail remain in full effect.

Attorney Sylvan Jaspen in court, defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo not in court, in custody.  Michael R Staskunas appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Case in court for bail/bond hearing.  State informed the Court that they have satisfied victims' rights law.  Bail motion by defense argued and granted by the Court.  Court set a status date upon request from the defense.  This case will be heard via Zoom. Zoom meeting information provided to parties.  This hearing may be streamed live on Dacast at the Court's discretion:  https://iframe.dacast.com/live/4dafbf46-ed15-c11c-fa22-a58262833632/a8cc2343-9b62-c309-778f-fa846faecb6a.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Status conference scheduled for September 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.

Request for Substitution of Judge received and filed.  Court consented to substitution against Judge Wagner.  Parties are advised the Clerk of Circuit Court reassigned case pursuant to current court rules to Judge Shelton, Br. 40.

Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo in court with Attorney Sylvan Jaspen.  Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo in custody.  Abby Rockendorf appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PARTIES APPEAR BY VIDEO.
Preliminary hearing proceeded.  Sworn for the State: Detectives J. Jopp and J. Ivy. State rests.  Defense rests.  Defense motion to dismiss argued and denied. Court found probable cause and bound defendant over for trial.  Original information received and filed;  defendant given a copy, waived reading, was arraigned in open court and plead not guilty. Defense to be heard on bail on the next date. Case is adjourned to Branch 40.  Bail/bond hearing scheduled for August 2, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Received and Filed: Attorney Sylvan Jaspen
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 5.  No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.
No Contact Order signed and filed.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with MMB, RTC, ACS.

Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo in court with attorney Sam Obscherning.  Defendant Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo in custody.  Dax Odom appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Yaniel Matos-Carrasquillo appeared by video means with Attorney.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Judge Wagner, Branch 38.  Defendant given a copy of the complaint and advised of maximum penalties, right to counsel and right to a preliminary hearing.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause to hold the defendant for further proceedings.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND PUBLIC DEFENDER WILL PROVIDE COUNSEL.  All parties are notified that effective July 30, 2022 this case will be assigned to Judge Laura A. Crivello, Branch 36,  in Room 608 of the Courthouse.  Commissioner advised DNA sample has been obtained from the Defendant.  Court advised Defendant he may qualify to have the DNA sample data expunged if he meets the conditions under Wisconsin Statutes Section 165.77(4).  Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 28, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.

Arrest Warrant received from the D.A.'s office on filing date of Criminal Complaint.
